@graph.schema:description: Event Domain Specification is a domain-specific pattern that represents a set of the classes, object and data properties needed for semantic annotation of different types of events (e.g. DanceEvent, BusinessEvent) including event offers (e.g. event tickets).
@graph.schema:name: Event

sh:property.rdfs:comment: Additional or internal identifier of the event.
The URL of an event. To indicate the resource, which published an event.
To represent detail information about an event. It should match the description of the event on the web page.

To represent image(s) associated with an event. If you don't have additional information about the image, such as size, license, copyright, choose a range "URL" to provide only the link to the image, otherwise select "ImageObject".
Additional or internal identifier for an image.
The URL of an image related to the annotated web page.
URL that provides a directly retrievable instance of the ImageObject.
The height of an image in pixels.
The width of an image in pixels.
Specifies the name of the image copyright owner, which can be a person or organization.
Every event must have a date and time when it starts, e.g. "2021-07-01T10:00:00"
To indicate a date, or date and timewhen an event will be finished, e.g. "2021-07-01" or 2021-07-01T10:00:00"
To indicate the door time of an event.
This property specifies the full name of a language, e.g. English.
This property specifies the formal language code tag expressed in BCP 47, e.g. EN.
